## PANDA_Analyze.py

Frozen.

No experimental validation code shall ever be added.

Only bug fixes are permitted.

Bug fix applied (2026-07-06): the charge-threshold bin range was
hardcoded to `np.logspace(-3, 3, 400)` (0.001-1000 fC), tuned against
the small default geometry (10um sensitiveXY). `np.histogram` silently
DROPS values outside the bin range rather than clipping them into the
edge bins, so any run with a larger sensitive volume depositing more
than 1000 fC -- e.g. a 500x500x50um geometry, which deposits up to
~3730 fC -- had those events vanish from the differential spectrum,
cumulative probability/cross-section curves, and CSV output entirely,
with no error or warning (only the printed Max statistic, computed
independently of the histogram, would hint at it). Bins are now sized
from a first pass over the true observed min/max per run instead of a
fixed range. Verified: the 500x500x50um case now correctly bins out to
~3654 fC, and the small default geometry reproduces its previously-
verified statistics exactly (no regression).

