# 15. Long-Term Vision

PANDA is intended to become a validated, publication-quality Monte Carlo framework for studying charge deposition by energetic particles in semiconductor materials.

The long-term objective is to reproduce classic detector-response experiments while providing a modern Geant4-based alternative to historical tools such as CUPID.

Experimental validation is considered equally important as simulation capability.

